    {
      "parameters": {
        "description": "Name: Personalized Content Generator (ROC-T-TOC Prompting)\n\nDescription:\nThis tool transforms structured user inputs (profile, CV, references, purpose, audience, style, tone, language) into a single user message + system message pair optimized for LLMs.\n\nThe System Message defines the AI agent’s persona: a professional writing assistant that always respects the user’s intent, audience, and style preferences.\n\nThe User Message injects dynamic data collected from forms or webhooks (e.g., CV text, references, academic/work info, content purpose). It follows the ROC-T-TOC framework (Role, Objective, Context, Task, Tone, Output, Constraints).\n\nPurpose:\nTo generate personalized, high-quality written content (e.g., job applications, project showcases, research posts) that:\n\nAligns with the user’s stated purpose.\n\nTargets the selected audience.\n\nReflects chosen writing style and tone.\n\nIntegrates raw CV and reference material when available.\n\nOutput:\nOne clean draft text (400–600 words by default) in the requested language, ready for direct use by the end user — no meta commentary, no JSON, no system noise."
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolThink",
      "typeVersion": 1.1,
      "position": [
        3056,
        1184
      ],
      "id": "c8386972-1d92-4472-a4cd-d43241372841",
      "name": "Think"
    },
